al, political, sexual, theatrical — his career intersects many of the hidden worlds of the eighteenth century. This narrative of detection brings together a hoard of newly discovered manuscripts to construct his many lives.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aTheatrical managerszEnglandzLondonvBiography. 4aLiterature Studies 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Modern / 18th Century .2bisacsh  aCovent Garden theatre.  aSecret Service.  aThomas Harris.  aeighteenth-century London.  agovernment news.  aphilanthropist.  aradicalism.  asexual suspect.  atheatre management.1 aOakley, Warren, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packagez978311128277040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152612913040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526129130423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526129130/original  a978-3-11-128277-0  Manchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packageb2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles